emails.subject: Fwd: India Open Hackathon - OPTIMIZE. ACCELERATE. SCALE
emails.content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Dean SEAS - SRM AP <dean.seas@srmap.edu.in>
Date: Thu, Aug 14, 2025, 11:21 PM
Subject: India Open Hackathon - OPTIMIZE. ACCELERATE. SCALE
To: All SEAS Students <students.seas@srmap.edu.in>
Cc: Faculty of Computer Science and Engineering <faculty.cse@srmap.edu.in>


FYI and participation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Together with NVIDIA and the OpenACC organization, the India Open
Hackathon is scheduled for 22nd Sept - 26th Sept. This is a unique
opportunity to advance HPC & AI projects with the help of dedicated
experts and seek collaboration with industry experts.

*Why participate?*  Open Hackathons and NVIDIA have had huge success
helping developers and research groups push their real-world projects
forward by connecting participants with the latest technologies, robust
tool sets, and collective expertise needed to advance their HPC & AI use
cases under the guidance of experts from industry.

Additionally, attendees have an opportunity to explore:
 Access to powerful leadership-class compute cluster systems with latest GPU architecture
Access to NVIDIA and partner mentors
Certificates

*Who can participate?* Any team comprising enthusiastic developers or
researchers (minimum of 2 people, maximum 5 people) with impactful
projects across a range of disciplines, including but not limited to:AI
for Scientific Domains
 AI for Governance
Quantum Computing
Generative and Agentic AI
AI in health sciences
Scientific Simulation at Scale

Space is limited: Calls close on *19th August*. *Apply now **here
<https://www.openhackathons.org/s/siteevent/a0CUP00001FSe3d2AD/se000392>*.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--
Prof. Chakkalakal V Tomy
Dean-School of Engineering and Sciences
☎: 0863 234 3454
📧: dean.seas@srmap.edu.in
🕷️: www.srmap.edu.in

ACCELERATE. SCALE To: All SEAS Students Cc: Faculty of Computer Science and Engineering FYI and participation ---------------------------------------------------------------------------= --------------- Together with NVIDIA and the OpenACC organization, the India Open Hackathon is scheduled for 22nd Sept - 26th Sept. This is a unique opportunity to advance HPC & AI projects with the help of dedicated experts and seek collaboration with industry experts. *Why participate?* Open Hackathons and NVIDIA have had huge success helping developers and research groups push their real-world projects forward by connecting participants with the latest technologies, robust tool sets, and collective expertise needed to advance their HPC & AI use cases under the guidance of experts from industry. Additionally, attendees have an opportunity to explore: Access to powerful leadership-class compute cluster systems with latest GPU architecture Access to NVIDIA and partner mentors Certificates *Who can participate?* Any team comprising enthusiastic developers or researchers (minimum of 2 people, maximum 5 people) with impactful projects across a range of disciplines, including but not limited to:AI for Scientific Domains AI for Governance Quantum Computing Generative and Agentic AI AI in health sciences Scientific Simulation at Scale Space is limited: Calls close on *19th August*. *Apply now **here *. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------= ------ --=20 [image: photograph] Prof. Chakkalakal V Tomy *Dean*-School of Engineering and Sciences =E2=98=8E: 0863 234 3454 *=F0=9F=93=A7**:* dean.seas@srmap.edu.in =F0=9F=95=B7=EF=B8=8F: www.srmap.edu.in --0000000000004e81fb063c5bc2b6 Content-Type: text/html; charset="UTF-8" Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

emails.subject: Welcome to your Azure for Students account
emails.content:
Start using your USD100* credit on popular products.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        

Start using your Azure for Students credit

Welcome to Azure for Students! Your account includes a USD100 credit, good for up to a year. Use your credit to try popular Azure products including virtual machines, artificial intelligence, and databases.

Get started >

Build the skills you need for your career with free, hands-on learning modules in Microsoft Learn. You get instant, in-browser access to Microsoft tools, so modules don’t count against your USD100 Azure for Students credit.

Account information

Subscription ID: 3c48a332-4b3c-4ef1-823e-4f3debedf7c4

Subscription name: Azure for Students

*Depending on the country in which you sign up for your Azure account, you may receive this credit in a specified local currency.

Privacy Statement

Microsoft Corporation, One Microsoft Way, ​Redmond, WA 98052​

emails.subject: Show them you're a proud Indian 🇮🇳
emails.content:
Design Independence Day creatives with stunning templates in Adobe Express.
This
Independence Day, set your creativity free.
It’s time to flaunt your national pride. Create eye-grabbing festive offer posts from hundreds of ready-to-use templates in Adobe Express. Customise as per your needs, add quick animations, and experience creative freedom at your fingertips.
Celebrate freedom
Special Pricing for India
Create your best work and take on more projects with world-class creative apps and time-saving generative AI features, all available in one simple Creative Cloud Pro subscription.
Get started
